.TH PPP 1 "2026-03-23" "ppp" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ppp \- universal pipe pretty-printer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B <command> | ppp
.RI [ flags ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ppp
reads from stdin, auto-detects the data format, and pretty-prints it with
syntax highlighting. No flags needed \(em just pipe to
.BR ppp .
.PP
The first 8KB of input is sampled to determine the format. Each built-in
detector returns a confidence score; the highest confidence wins.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-format " " \fIfmt\fR
Force a specific format, skipping auto-detection.
Valid values:
.BR json ", " yaml ", " csv ", " tsv ", " xml ", " html ", "
.BR toml ", " jwt ", " base64 ", " urlencoded ", " log .
.TP
.B \-\-inspect
Output detection metadata as JSON to stdout, then exit. The output is a JSON
object with
.B format
and
.B confidence
fields.
.TP
.B \-\-strict
Exit with status 2 if detection confidence is low or none. Can be combined with
.BR \-\-inspect .
.TP
.B \-\-no\-color
Disable colored output.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print help and exit.
.SH FORMATS
.TS
l l.
json	JSON objects and arrays
yaml	YAML documents
csv	Comma-separated values
tsv	Tab-separated values
xml	XML documents
html	HTML documents
toml	TOML configuration files
jwt	JSON Web Tokens (decoded header + payload)
base64	Base64-encoded data (decoded, inner format detected)
urlencoded	URL-encoded key=value pairs
log	Log lines with timestamps and levels
.TE
.SH DETECTION ORDER
Detectors run in this priority order. On a tie, the earlier detector wins.
.PP
.nf
1. JWT \(em three dot-separated base64url segments
2. JSON \(em starts with { or [, valid parse
3. XML/HTML \(em starts with <
4. YAML \(em --- or key: value patterns
5. TOML \(em [section] + key = value
6. CSV/TSV \(em consistent delimiter counts
7. URL-encoded \(em key=value&key=value
8. Log lines \(em timestamp + level patterns
9. Base64 \(em valid charset, decodes to UTF-8
10. Plain text \(em fallback passthrough
.fi
.SH EXAMPLES
Pretty-print a JSON API response:
.PP
.nf
curl -s https://api.example.com/users | ppp
.fi
.PP
Pretty-print a YAML config:
.PP
.nf
cat config.yaml | ppp
.fi
.PP
Force CSV format:
.PP
.nf
cat data.csv | ppp -f csv
.fi
.PP
Decode a JWT:
.PP
.nf
echo 'eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJzdWIiOiIxIn0.sig' | ppp
.fi
.PP
Colorize Docker logs:
.PP
.nf
docker logs myapp | ppp
.fi
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
If set, disables colored output (see https://no-color.org).
.SH COLOR
Color is automatically disabled when stdout is not a terminal (e.g., piping
to a file or another command), or when the
.B NO_COLOR
environment variable is set.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
An error occurred reading stdin or formatting output.
.TP
.B 2
Low detection confidence (only with
.BR \-\-strict ).
